ost_step.1: On Saturday, Paul filled up 6 bags with cans. Each bag can hold 8 cans.
ost_step.2: Therefore, on Saturday Paul picked up 6 bags * 8 cans/bag = 48 cans.

direct_answer.text: Paul picked up 48 cans on Saturday. Then he picked up 3 more bags full of cans, so he picked up 3 bags * 8 cans/bag = 24 cans on Sunday. In total, Paul picked up 48 + 24 = 72 cans.
